Box 82521 Lincoln, Nebraska 68501-2521 SEP 28 1998 PUBLIC COPY Refer To File No. LIN 98-180-52148 NARAIN D SIKRI C/O SANDIP SIKRI 6 WINDMILL CT SILVER SPRINGS MD 20905 DECISION Upon consideration, it is ordered that your Application for Travel Document be denied for the following reasons: "SEE ATTACHMENT" You may, if you wish, appeal this decision. You must submit such an appeal to THIS OFFICE with a filing fee of $110.00. If you do not file an appeal within the time allowed, this decision is final. Appeal in your case may be made to: The Board of Immigration Appeals (Board) in Falls Church, Virginia. It must reach this office within 15 calendar days from the date this notice is served (18 days if this notice is mailed). X The Administrative Appeals Unit (AAU) in Washington, D.C. It must reach this office within 30 calendar days from the date this notice is served (33 days if this notice is mailed) . Do NOT send your appeal directly to the Board or to the AAU. Please direct any questions you may have to the Immigration and Naturalization Service office nearest your residence. Natalie Vedder Director Enclosure (s) I-290B LIN/JSL/IIO
